/PGSIMH/±AT TORAH/XX654/XX/PR

/KAHAKAFOT / THE PROCESSIONS FOR/PR

SIMH/±AT TORAH/XX/PR

You have proclaimed for all to know, that /SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX is

God, there is none else,/PR

the one who alone performed great, wondrous deeds,/PR


whose love is everlasting./PR

There is none like you among the powerful, /SCE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX,/PR


and there are no deeds like your deeds./PR

May the glory of /SCT/XXHE /XXO/XXNE/XX be everlasting,/PR


may /SCT/XXHE /XXO/XXNE/XX take joy in the creation,/PR

may the name of /SCT/XXHE /XXA/XXLMIGHTY /XXO/XXNE/XX be blessed,/PR


now and forever./PR

May /SCT/XXHE /XXH/XXOLY /XXO/XXNE/XX, our God, be with us,/PR


just as it happened for our ancestors!/PR


Do not forsake nor turn away from God./PR

But say: "Redeem us, God of our redemption,/PR


and unite us, save us from our foes,/PR

so that your holy name may be acknowledged,/PR


and that we may share a portion of your glory."/PR

/SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX reigns!/PR

/SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX has always reigned!/PR

/SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX shall reign beyond all time./PR

/SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX gives strength to our people./PR

May /SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX bless us with peace./PR

And may our words be seen with favor/PR


by the One who watches over all./PI/PR

